        <h1>Mark 7: Breakdown and Deeper Meaning</h1>
        <p><strong>Mark 7 is a powerful chapter where Jesus confronts religious traditions, exposes the true source of sin, and extends His mission beyond Israel.</strong></p>

        <h2>1. Jesus Confronts the Pharisees on Tradition (Mark 7:1-23)</h2>
        <p><strong>Context:</strong> The Pharisees criticize Jesus’ disciples for eating with unwashed hands, prioritizing oral traditions over God's commandments.</p>
        <p><strong>Key Teachings:</strong></p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Hypocrisy of Man-Made Religion:</strong> Jesus quotes Isaiah 29:13, condemning their empty worship.</li>
            <li><strong>True Defilement Comes from Within:</strong> Sin is from the heart, not external actions (Mark 7:20-23).</li>
            <li><strong>Jesus Overturns Food Laws:</strong> This foreshadows Acts 10:15.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. The Faith of the Syrophoenician Woman (Mark 7:24-30)</h2>
        <p><strong>Context:</strong> A Gentile woman begs Jesus to heal her daughter.</p>
        <p><strong>The Controversial Exchange:</strong> Jesus tests her faith, and she humbly responds, proving that God’s mercy is for all.</p>
        <p><strong>Deeper Meaning:</strong></p>
        <ul>
            <li>Faith, not nationality, grants access to God's blessings.</li>
            <li>Jesus foreshadows salvation for all nations (Matthew 28:19).</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Jesus Heals a Deaf and Mute Man (Mark 7:31-37)</h2>
        <p><strong>Context:</strong> Jesus heals a man in a personal, physical way.</p>
        <p><strong>Deeper Meaning:</strong></p>
        <ul>
            <li>Jesus’ miracles are deeply personal.</li>
            <li>Physical healing symbolizes spiritual healing.</li>
            <li>Fulfills Isaiah 35:5-6, proving Jesus is the Messiah.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Overall Takeaways:</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Religious tradition should never replace God's Word.</li>
            <li>Sin is an internal issue, not just external actions.</li>
            <li>God's mercy is available to all who have faith.</li>
            <li>Jesus is the Messiah who heals physically and spiritually.</li>
        </ul>

